# PM Agent Evolution Log

Tracks key changes across iterations (last 10 entries).

---
[2026-04-20] Run #1: First PM analysis. Discovered domain (autonomous GitHub workflow agents), mapped capabilities (4 agents, 8 protocols, ~1400 LOC), conducted market research (AutoGPT, CrewAI, Devin, Linear AI competitors). Generated 26 proposals across Core Logic (8), API (6), Docs (6), DX (6). Key gaps identified: no README, no tests, no observability, single-repo limitation. Created issues #8-#33.
[2026-04-20] Run #2: Production readiness focus. Updated capabilities analysis (3 merged PRs: PM agent, review workflow, FLOW B optimization). Analyzed code for reliability gaps (13 unguarded CLI calls, 61 hard-coded labels, 47 console.log statements, no error handling). Conducted Run #2 market research (Sweep AI added resilience, GitHub Copilot Workspace added approval gates, Linear AI launched enterprise tier). Generated 20 NEW proposals across Core Logic (8), API (4), Docs (4), DX (4). Key themes: Error handling, configuration system, structured logging, security, agent lifecycle management. Differentiation: Local-first + production-grade (unique combo). Run #1 focused on features, Run #2 focuses on reliability as unlock for enterprise adoption.
[2026-04-23] Run #3: Completion-focused analysis (3 days after Run #2). Discovered: Partial implementation syndrome (5 commits but all incomplete: API retry ✅, CLI retry ❌, init check ✅, init fix ❌, README ✅, tests ❌). Identified proposal quality crisis (50+ pm-proposals, 100% marked "needs-info"). Market research confirms "Post-Q1 Reliability Reckoning" trend. Generated 8 HYPER-SPECIFIC proposals (vs. 20 in Run #2, 26 in Run #1). Strategic pivot: Quality over quantity, completion over creation, dogfooding credibility. Key priorities: (1) Complete GitHub CLI error handling, (2) Triage test suite (proof-of-concept), (3) Cost tracking telemetry MVP, (4) Interactive init script. Themes: Finish partial work, prove differentiation (cost savings visibility), unlock trust (dogfooding tests), improve PM agent itself (meta-validation).
[2026-04-26] Run #4: Leverage & Deploy focus. Discovered: Massive velocity (7+ commits Apr 24-25). NEW Reviewer agent (telemetry tracking). Testing infrastructure shipped (Vitest + CI). Git worktrees merged (PR #74). pnpm migration complete. Needs-info rate gating enforced (<20%). Generated 2 HYPER-SPECIFIC proposals (vs. 8 in Run #3): (1) Cost Dashboard (leverage Reviewer telemetry, make moat visible), (2) Deployment Guide (enterprise unblock, cron/CI/cloud). Both scored 100/100 validation. Created issues #79-#80. Strategic insight: Telemetry infrastructure exists, needs presentation layer. Production deployment guides missing (enterprise blocker). Portfolio health: 0 open pm-proposals (cleaned from 51), 50 closed (bulk cleanup Apr 24-25). Quality over quantity trend continues.
[2026-04-26] Run #5: Automation & Enterprise Readiness focus. Discovered: Run #4 proposals (#79 Cost Dashboard, #80 Deployment Guide) in progress. Identified PREREQUISITE gap: Deployment guide documents "run in cron", but cron can't handle multi-step manual workflows. Generated 1 CRITICAL proposal: Auto-Orchestrator (#82) - enables hands-off automation (issue → PR, no manual triggers). Scored 100/100. Strategic insight: Orchestrator is foundation for production deployment (#80 depends on it). Competitive parity: GitHub Copilot Workspace auto-chains, Sweep AI auto-executes - orchestrator closes last automation gap. Portfolio health: 0 open pm-proposals maintained, 1 created this run. Skipped PHASE 0 (not 3rd run) and PHASE 1 (no rejected proposals to revalidate). Quality over quantity trend continues (1 proposal vs. 2 in Run #4, 8 in Run #3).
